result.name: Chan Kan Kee Chiu Chow Restaurant

reviews.text: Nice authentic chiu chow cuisine, staff werent really nice..

Great local cuisine. We opted for simple dishes as this was what we were looking for. Vegetarian fried rice and seasonal stir fried vegetables with garlic and ginger. Very delicious, a little on the expensive side for what it was.

I suppose the place could be good if you are not a foreigner. My roast goose was served completely cold.  I also didn’t get a pot of tea like all the other local customers, but just a pour in a dirty mug (but still paid for it!) The service and the experience was completely awful, I very much regret going there.
We had lunch and tried noodles and rice. They were both very good. I would recommend it.
If you like Chiu Chow this place is not bad.  Oyster congee was awesome!

result.formatted_address: 11 Queen's Rd W, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Chan Kan Kee Chiu Chow Restaurant

reviews.text:
Hands down one of the best goose I’ve eaten in Hong Kong. This goose is cooked in soya sauce instead of the traditional roasted kind.

We ordered the ¼ goose leg, boiled lungs soup and stir fried vegetables which all tasted super amazing. The vegetables was not bitter at all and had a sweet taste to it. The soup tasted like it was boiled for at least 24h to get the flavor of its ingredients out. And the star of the restaurant, the goose was moist and tender and flavorful .

I’ll definitely say this place is a bit expensive but in my opinion worth the price. You get quality food and service at the price you pay. Our meal cost us 500HKD and it was worth it.

Give this place a try and you won’t regret.

100% Tourist trap 
Only tourists who doesn’t know Chinese food would go.
Terribly overpriced approx. 3x or 4x reasonable price for this quality
Very nice Chiu Chow food as I’m from Chiu Chow as well. Recommended

Poor services with fair price of food. Ordered panfried fish and egg, veggie with squid, taro in duck and oyster congee. The waitress/ owner arranged to be seated at a one  sided table with one of the seats explosed to intense air-conditioning. So I requested to change to another table under no windy environment. The waiter sent the dishes in a rude or careless manner as he simply placed the dish on the table and pushed it against others without making any rearrangement. The congee and duck were just warm when it's placed at my table.
